        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 6:43PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 643 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Uptown Charlotte, moving north at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Charlotte, Freedom Park, The Plaza, Charlotte Douglas Airport, Paw
Creek, and Croft.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
